b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Smartsheet and Sunsama share a solid foundation of core features including Task Management, Ai Assistant, Calendar, Integrations. Where Smartsheet pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Collaboration and Automation and Templates, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Smartsheet holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Sunsama scores 7/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Smartsheet offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $9/mo, compared to Sunsama's starting price of $20/mo. Neither platform offers a free plan, so you will need to budget for at least the starting tier from the beginning. Be sure to take advantage of any trial periods they may offer."}]]}]
