f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Smartsheet is best suited for PMOs, construction, enterprise operations, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Sunsama, meanwhile, shines for individuals, executives, mindful workers, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2005, Smartsheet describes itself as \"Spreadsheet-based work management platform with AI automation for enterprises.\" Sunsama, established in 2016, positions itself as \"Calm daily planner that pulls tasks from all your tools into one focused view.\" With 11 years between them, Smartsheet brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Sunsama offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Smartsheet** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 6), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Sunsama is a poor choice — far from it. Sunsama excels in its own right, particularly for individuals and executives.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value familiar spreadsheet interface, go with Smartsheet. If beautiful daily planning ritual matters more to you, Sunsama is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
